tary cell tumours account for the majority of cases","Growth hormone deficiency only affects children","Secondary hypothyroidism is more common than primary hypothyroidism","Gonadotropin deficiency causes increased libido","Diabetes insipidus occurs in all cases"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn hypopituitarism, \u003Cstrong\u003Epituitary cell tumours\u003C/strong\u003E account for the majority (~60%) of cases. This is the correct answer.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGrowth hormone deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E affects both children and adults, leading to poor growth in children and metabolic effects in adults. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESecondary hypothyroidism\u003C/strong\u003E due to pituitary dysfunction is less common than primary hypothyroidism. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGonadotropin deficiency\u003C/strong\u003E leads to decreased libido, not increased. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes insipidus\u003C/strong\u003E only occurs if the posterior pituitary is affected, which is not always the case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe diagnosis requires careful hormonal evaluation including stimulation tests, as well as imaging to investigate for mass lesions. \u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pituitary cell tumours are the primary cause of hypopituitarism","Visual field defects should be assessed for in cases of hypopituitarism where a mass lesion is suspected or known"],"references":["Kim SY. Diagnosis and Treatment of Hypopituitarism. Endocrinol Metab (Seoul). 2015 Dec;30(4):443-55. doi: 10.3803/EnM.2015.30.4.443. PMID: 26790380; PMCID: PMC4722397","Beysel S, \u00c7ali\u015fkan M, Kizilg\u00fcl M, Kan S, \u00d6zbek M, \u00c7akal E. Clinical evaluation of pituitary insufficiency in adult population. Turk J Med Sci. 2020 Jun 23;50(4):917-921. doi: 10.3906/sag-1908-19. PMID: 32283895; PMCID: PMC7379402","Gounden V, Anastasopoulou C, Jialal I. Hypopituitarism. [Updated 2023 Sep 16]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK470414/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65977"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15620"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65977","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65977"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-22T09:28:28+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-22T09:29:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8311"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80681"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id"